[{"location":"writing/#Writing","page":"Writing","title":"Writing","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"writing/","page":"Writing","title":"Writing","text":"HTMLTables.table\nHTMLTables.write\nHTMLTables.jpg\nHTMLTables.pdf\nHTMLTables.png","category":"page"},{"location":"writing/#HTMLTables.table","page":"Writing","title":"HTMLTables.table","text":"HTMLTables.table(\n    tbl;\n    header::Bool=true,\n    footer::Bool=true,\n    id::String=\"\",\n    classes::String=\"\",\n    css::Bool=true,\n    theme::String=\"default\",\n    colorscale=\"\",\n    tooltips::Bool=true\n)\n\nReturns a julia table as an HTML table.\n\nArguments\n\ntbl: The table to write.\nfilename: The filename of the HTML table.\nsave_location: The location to save the HTML table.\nheader: Whether to include the table header.\nfooter: Whether to include the table footer.\nid: The id of the HTML table.\nclasses: The classes of the HTML table.\ncss: Whether to include the CSS styles.\ntheme: The theme of the HTML table.\ncolorscale: The colorscale of the HTML table.\ntooltips: Whether to include tooltips.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"writing/#HTMLTables.write","page":"Writing","title":"HTMLTables.write","text":"HTMLTables.write(\n    tbl;\n    filename::String=\"table\",\n    save_location::String=Base.Filesystem.pwd(),\n    kwargs...\n)\n\nWrites a julia table as an HTML table to an HTML file.\n\nArguments\n\ntbl: The table to write.\nfilename: The filename of the HTML table.\nsave_location: The location to save the HTML table.\nheader: Whether to include the table header.\nfooter: Whether to include the table footer.\nid: The id of the HTML table.\nclasses: The classes of the HTML table.\ncss: Whether to include the CSS styles.\ntheme: The theme of the HTML table.\ncolorscale: The colorscale of the HTML table.\ntooltips: Whether to include tooltips.\n\nReturns\n\npath: The path to the HTML file.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"writing/#HTMLTables.jpg","page":"Writing","title":"HTMLTables.jpg","text":"HTMLTables.jpg(tbl; kwargs...)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"writing/#HTMLTables.pdf","page":"Writing","title":"HTMLTables.pdf","text":"HTMLTables.pdf(tbl; kwargs...)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"writing/#HTMLTables.png","page":"Writing","title":"HTMLTables.png","text":"HTMLTables.png(tbl; kwargs...)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"references/#References","page":"References","title":"References","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"references/","page":"References","title":"References","text":"Bezanson, J.; Edelman, A.; Karpinski, S. and Shah, V. B. (2017). Julia: A fresh approach to numerical computing. SIAM Review 59, 65–98. Publisher: SIAM.\n\n\n\nBouchet-Valat, M. and Kamiński, B. (2023). DataFrames.jl: Flexible and Fast Tabular Data in Julia. Journal of Statistical Software 107, 1–32.\n\n\n\nQuinn, J.; Anthoff, D.; Arakaki, T.; Kamiński, B.; Bouchet-Valat, M.; Papp, T. K.; Arslan, A.; ExpandingMan; Schouten, R.; Robinson, N.; Ferris, A.; Arkoniak; Sharma, A.; Davies, E.; Kalybek, E.; Lin, I.; Dunn, J.; Revels, J.; Day, J.; Calderón, J. B.; TagBot, J.; Samuel, O.; Vertechi, P.; Zwitch, R.; StatisticalMice and strickek (Jan 2021). JuliaData/Tables.jl: v1.3.1.\n\n\n\nQuinn, J.; O'Connor, S.; Malmaud, J.; Gadsden, D.; Dunning, I.; Fischer, K.; Ekre, F.; Hanson, L.; Espeset, D.; Allaun, Z.; Arslan, A.; Hennigh-Palermo, W. A.; Kelman, T.; White, F.; der Plas, F.; Art; Graaf, C.; Forgy, E.; Ha, C.; Anantharaman, R.; Sakai, A.; Drvoštěp, T.; Yu, Y.; Saba, E.; Mohapatra, T.; Hojda, M.; Driscoll, M.; Karpinski, S.; Donner, R. and Nash, J. (Mar 2024). JuliaWeb/HTTP.jl: v1.9.18.\n\n\n\n","category":"page"},{"location":"#HTMLTables","page":"Home","title":"HTMLTables","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"HTMLTables.HTMLTables","category":"page"},{"location":"#HTMLTables.HTMLTables","page":"Home","title":"HTMLTables.HTMLTables","text":"Julia package for reading, writing, and viewing HTML tables.\n\nReading HTML tables:\n\nHTMLTables.get reads an HTML table as a string.\nHTMLTables.read extracts data from HTML tables.\n\nWriting HTML tables:\n\nHTMLTables.table uses the Tables.jl interface to write an HTML table as a string.\nHTMLTables.write uses the Tables.jl interface to write an HTML table in a file.\nHTMLTables.jpg writes an HTML table as a JPG image.\nHTMLTables.pdf writes an HTML table as a PDF document.\nHTMLTables.png writes an HTML table as a PNG image.\n\nViewing HTML tables:\n\nHTMLTables.display displays a julia table as an HTML table in julia.\nHTMLTables.open opens a julia table as an HTML table in the browser.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"module"},{"location":"reading/#Reading","page":"Reading","title":"Reading","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"reading/","page":"Reading","title":"Reading","text":"HTMLTables.get\nHTMLTables.read","category":"page"},{"location":"reading/#HTMLTables.get","page":"Reading","title":"HTMLTables.get","text":"HTMLTables.get(source::String; id::String=\"\", classes::Union{Vector{String},String}=\"\", index::Int=1)\n\nReturns an HTML table a source as a string.\n\nArguments\n\nsource::String: URL or path to the HTML table.\nid::String: The id of the HTML table.\nclasses::Union{Vector{String},String}: The classes of the HTML table.\nindex::Int: The index of the HTML table in the HTML document.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"reading/#HTMLTables.read","page":"Reading","title":"HTMLTables.read","text":"HTMLTables.read(source::String; id::String=\"\", classes::Union{Vector{String},String}=\"\")\n\nReads a HTML table into a sink function such as DataFrame.\n\nArguments\n\nsource::String: URL or path to the HTML table.\nsink: The function that materializes the table data.\nid::String: The id of the HTML table.\nclasses::Union{Vector{String},String}: The classes of the HTML table.\nindex::Int: The index of the HTML table in the HTML document.\n\nExamples\n\n# reading an HTML table into a DataFrame\nusing HTMLTables, DataFrames\n\ndf = HTMLTables.read(\"https://www.w3schools.com/html/html_tables.asp\", DataFrame)\n\n# writing the html table data into a CSV file\nusing CSV\n\nCSV.write(\"table.csv\", df)\n\n# writing the html table data into a JSON file\nusing JSON, JSONTables\n\njson = JSONTables.objecttable(df)\n\nBase.open(\"table.json\", \"w\") do io\n    JSON3.pretty(io, json)\nend\n\n# writing the html table data into an Excel file\nusing XLSX\n\nXLSX.writetable(\"table.xlsx\", \"Sheet 1\" => df)\n\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"viewing/#Viewing","page":"Viewing","title":"Viewing","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"viewing/","page":"Viewing","title":"Viewing","text":"HTMLTables.open\nHTMLTables.display","category":"page"},{"location":"viewing/#HTMLTables.open","page":"Viewing","title":"HTMLTables.open","text":"HTMLTables.open(tbl; kwargs...)\n\nOpens a julia table as an HTML table in the browser.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"viewing/#HTMLTables.display","page":"Viewing","title":"HTMLTables.display","text":"HTMLTables.display(tbl; kwargs...)\n\nDisplays a julia table as an HTML table in julia.\n\nArguments\n\ntbl: The table to display.\nkwargs: Keyword arguments to pass to the HTMLTables.table function.\n\nExamples\n\nusing DataFrames, HTMLTables\n\ndf = DataFrame(\n    \"a\" => [001, 002, 003, 004, 005, 006, 007, 008, 009, 010],\n    \"b\" => [011, 012, 013, 014, 015, 016, 017, 018, 019, 020],\n    \"c\" => [021, 022, 023, 024, 025, 026, 027, 028, 029, 030],\n    \"d\" => [031, 032, 033, 034, 035, 036, 037, 038, 039, 040],\n    \"e\" => [041, 042, 043, 044, 045, 046, 047, 048, 049, 050],\n    \"f\" => [051, 052, 053, 054, 055, 056, 057, 058, 059, 060],\n    \"g\" => [061, 062, 063, 064, 065, 066, 067, 068, 069, 070],\n    \"h\" => [071, 072, 073, 074, 075, 076, 077, 078, 079, 080],\n    \"i\" => [081, 082, 083, 084, 085, 086, 087, 088, 089, 090],\n    \"j\" => [091, 092, 093, 094, 095, 096, 097, 098, 099, 100]\n)\n\nHTMLTables.display(df, theme=\"green\", colorscale=\"Greens\")\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"}]
